        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 4:58PM PDT by NWS Elko NV</headline>
        <description>At 457 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Ryndon, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Heavy rainfall along with gusty winds could knock down tree
limbs and blow around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage
to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Elko, Deeth, Ryndon, Spring Creek, and Halleck.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
